12/01/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative and EU Special Representative Christian Schwarz-Schilling was in Berlin on Thursday (January 11th). He met with German Chancellor Angela Merkel, whose country holds the rotating EU presidency. They focused on the latest developments in BiH, including the readiness of BiH authorities to assume day-to-day responsibilities without OHR support. They stressed that clear agreement on police reform is key to signing a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU. (OHR website, RTRS, PBS, Fena - 11/01/07)
